  { "id": "r023", "title": "Made to Stick", "category": "Consumer Psychology", "categoryId": "consumer-psychology", "author": "Chip Heath & Dan Heath", "publisher": "Random House", "publicationYear": "2008", "pageCount": 304, "isbn13": "9781407008240", "isbn10": "1407008242", "coverImage": "https://books.google.com/books/content?id=OUgCHkxZTX4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api", "infoLink": "https://books.google.com.eg/books?id=OUgCHkxZTX4C&dq=intitle:Made+to+Stick+inauthor:Chip+Heath&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api", "description": "A NEW YORK TIMES AND INTERNATIONAL BESTSELLER 'This book is a gift to anyone who needs to get a message across and make it stick.' New Statesman 'Smart, lively . . . such fun to read.' Guardian _________________________________________________ Mark Twain once observed, 'A lie can get halfway around the world before the truth can even get its boots on.' His observation rings true: urban legends, conspiracy theories, and bogus news stories circulate effortlessly. Meanwhile, people with important ideas - entrepreneurs, teachers, politicians, and journalists - struggle to make them 'stick'. In Made to Stick, Chip and Dan Heath reveal the anatomy of ideas that stick and explain how to make ideas..." },
